history.content: Enrollment limits have been adjusted according to enrollment predictions and budget constraints. You are right that in Fall '15 the enrollment limits were 40 each for undergrad and grad students, however that semester only 30 students total were enrolled. The undergrad section currently has a few open seats. Once graduate students have the chance to enroll, I will move any empty seat to the undergrad side to make more room or vice versa for the grad side.

In last several fall semesters, EE147 typically had a capacity of 40 for undergrads and 40 for graduate students (in 247A). However, this time it only has 25 seats for undergrads and 55 seats for graduate students. Will the capacity for undergrads be expanded this time? The undergrad-level class was even full a few days ago, which had never happened before.
history.subject: Will EE147 get expanded for undergrads?
